# tmux notes
 - `tmux new -s {name}`
	 - to start the session
***
## tmux controls

- `ctrl + r `
	- search through command history

- `ctrl + space`  or  `ctrl + p`
	- prefix key
	- only need to press and then the next key is the "modified" version
	- press it again to get out of the "modified" next key
	- is `ctrl + b` by default

- `prefix then c`
	- store the tab in background/create a new tab
	- current tab is the one with the star by it
	- will create a new tab to go to

- `prefix then {number}`
	- switches to tab with the number

- `exit`
	- in the command line to quit out of the shell

- `prefix then ,`
	- rename the tab


- `prefix then v`
	- split the terminal vertical
- `prefix then h`
	- split the terminal horizontal
- `prefix then arrow key`
	- to move around the splits
	- the current active split has dull green lines around it
	- `exit` to get out of the split 
- `prefix then shift + [`  and `prefix then shift + ]` 
	- moves tabs around
- `prefix then space` 
	- changes the layout of the tabs
	

- `prefix then [`
	- enter search/copy mode
	- makes it easier to read long outputs
	- can tell by the line number thing in top right
	- `pageup` and `pagedn` to go up and down full screens
	- `ctrl + c`  to exit this mode
	- `?`  (`shift + /`) to find up and `/`  find down
		- `shift + /` then type "red" to jump to top of output 
	- hit  `space` to start selecting from current position then hit  `enter`  to save and then `prefix then ]` to use

- `ctrl + a`
	- go to the beginning of the line
- `ctrl + e` 
	- go to the end of the line
- `ctrl + arrow key`
	- go in direction word by word

- `prefix then ?` aka `prefix then shift + /`
	- pulls up the ? menu

- `prefix then t`
	- puts the time in the command window

***
## tmux commands
- `tmux new-session -s {name}`
	- create a new session

- `tmux list-sessions`
	- to see all current sessions of tmux

- `tmux attach-session {session name}`
	- to reattach to a session

- `tmux kill-session -t {session name}`
	- kill the session with the name specified

- `tmux kill-server`
	- to kill every session of tmux running

***
## Other notes
- maybe smart to use this on server as an alt to screen



***
## .tmux.conf
```bash

#rebind prefix key
unbind C-b
set -g prefix C-Space
set -g prefix2 C-p

#allow mouse usage
#set -g mouse on

#rebind splitting the terminal
unbind v
unbind h
unbind % # Split vertically
unbind '"' # Split horizontally
bind v split-window -h -c "#{pane_current_path}"
bind h split-window -v -c "#{pane_current_path}"

#qol stuff
set -g history-limit 100000
set -g allow-rename off

#set search mode to vi
set-window-option -g mode-keys vi

```
